<TITLE> Cold wave easing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 9 (bdnews24.com)  The prevailing cold wave sweeping over the northeastern part of Bangladesh is slowly easing off, the Meteorological Department said Saturday. The biting cold would abate from Sunday, the forecast said. A 24 hour forecast said that the moderate cold wave blowing over Srimangal, Comilla and Feni districts would turn into a mild one on Sunday. Met office duty meteorologist of the Rasheduzzaman told bdnews24.com, "The temperature will increase gradually. The mild cold wave also will also gradually die away within the next few days." However, the long range weather forecast says that two more moderate cold waves might sweep through the country by the end of January. The lowest temperature to date this winter was recorded as 6 degrees Celsius in Srimangal on Jan 9. The same low was recorded in Jessore last month, on Dec 29. bdne
